<br>
Secondly, something for Shintou.<br>
<br>
I haven't been on the board for a few days, so I just caught up with all the mess.  Things sure sprout up fast, don't they?  You only met my character Sneaux twice.  I remember both times quite well.  The first time was at Nysa's birthing.  You showed up and caused a lot of hell.  In fact, I think Morgen defeated you in one of your many duels that night.<br>
<br>
The second time, and I don't really know if you remember this, was with Rowynia in Felwithe.  We ran into you quite by accident.  And our exchange was quick.  You looked me over, decided I wasn't worth the 2 seconds it would have taken for you to slaughter me in a duel (which you would have) and you threw a few insults at me and Rowy and faded into the shadows.<br>
<br>
I remember both these encounters because your roleplaying had a profound impact on my roleplaying EQ as well.  With longevity of character comes a bigger and bigger enemies list, as I'm sure you know.  And the end result of that tends to be situations like you've been having with other players, as already seen above.<br>
<br>
I hope you enjoy the break from EQ that you're taking, but I sincerely hope that you continue to roleplay with us here, as I have done in my retirement, so that we may all enjoy your Roleplaying style.  <br>
<br>
It should be said that we all have the freedom to choose wether or not we play with someone.  I'd say that I would choose to play with you again someday.<br>
<br>
Respectively,<br>
<br>
Sneaux Di'Angelis<br>
