<br>
Ah, Shintou.  The player I've heard nothing but good things about.  Until recently, that is.<br>
<br>
However, I have enjoyed every exchange we have had so far in the game.  That time when you were disillusioned with the world, Jaranna felt really sorry for Shintou (and I felt sorry for the player, as he was probably disillusioned with the removal of some rules, as well).<br>
<br>
Then there's the time when we met in the bank and you slapped me.  Then I just walked away.  Jaranna's not weak.  She just knows when she's unable to win, and she tries to avoid those situations.<br>
<br>
Jaranna is planning on fighting you again someday.  I want to get up to 59 and trade harm touches with you. *grins*<br>
<br>
But the problem is that Jaranna is involved with Vivienne.  And so, we walk a fine line here.  If you want to RP with me as a member of the Circle of Sisters, then that's great.  I'm all for it.<br>
<br>
But I ask that you do not bring up Vivienne in said RP.  Leave her out of it, as she has requested.  Hate me for being in the Lightbringer guild, and ignore the fact that Jaranna's married (or will be soon) to Vivienne.<br>
<br>
I've really enjoyed our interactions thus far, and I hope they can continue when you return.  I've had no problems with you--just the way your girlfriend stated her thoughts on the SoM board. *shrugs*<br>
<br>
Thanks for the fun so far.<br>
