<br>
That bastard harm touched her.  He just reached out and laid a finger on her shoulder, killing her as she tried to run away.<br>
<br>
Jaranna screamed in frustration.  Who the hell was this guy?  Was he evil incarnate, as he claimed to be?  No, Jaranna thought.  He's a good fighter, but he's not Evil itself.  But, evil he is, and he balances some good.  So, he is necessary to the balance of this world.<br>
<br>
&quot;Damn it!&quot;  Jaranna looked around, but the only soul in the room with her was the cursed traveller, staring deep into the fire in the middle of the room.<br>
<br>
Jaranna tuned her thoughts to those of her comrades.  &quot;Um...so.  Is he violating my cold corpse yet?&quot;  The answer came back to her.  He had taken the bodies to Freeport and posted them in front of the guild hall the same way he displayed the broken body of Delmarahl.<br>
<br>
She looked around and found the firepot with Freeport's city insignia and touched it, instantly transporting to the docks.  People stared as she walked through the streets, and Jaranna looked around, wondering what they were looking at.<br>
<br>
Then she looked down, and she noticed that she was naked except for her body jewelry.  She started to cover herself, then thought better of it.  &quot;Might as well give these people a show.&quot;  She walked on to the guild hall.<br>
<br>
She looked up at the broken corpse, then pushed it over, pulling a robe from her bag and donning it.  Then she pulled all her clothing, jewelry and belongings from the carcass. But before she took the last item, she looked at the body.  She saw the pain--the surprise--in its eyes.  Then she took her sewing kit, and the body decomposed before her eyes.<br>
<br>
&quot;Balance or not, I will kill him.  Just as he killed me.  Next time he faces me, he will find a stronger wizard.  One with more powerful spells, faster legs, and the wisdom one can only glean from defeat.&quot;<br>
<br>
Jaranna grabbed a passing citizen by the shoulders and looked him in the eyes.  &quot;He wants to harm touch me?!  We'll see how he likes to be harm touched!&quot;  Jaranna let the wide-eyed citizen go, then ran off toward the Desert of Ro.<br>
<br>
-------------------<br>
<br>
&quot;First things first.  I must become powerful enough to implement a Mana Burn.  So, I must learn.&quot;<br>
<br>
Jaranna spotted a spiroc running along the beach.  She casta spell, slowing it down to a crawl, and she ran in front of it, teasing it with her staff before casting her most powerful spell and watching its feathers burn in a beautiful orange and yellow conflagration.<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes....  Learn.  And when the time comes, Shintou Shinai, you will feel the power of MY harm touch.&quot; <p><P>Jaranna<BR>
Circle of Sisters</P>
<P><EM>Raven hair and ruby lips<BR>
Sparks fly from her finger tips<BR>
Echoed voices in the night<BR>
She's a restless spirit on an endless flight</EM></P></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=20371A><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/uroninsenshi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RoninSenshi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#660000>(9/19/02 8:35:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fcircleofsistersfrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=292.topic&index=28>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_biglaugh.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Two Important Notes</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  She should find her corspe unmolested, ironically. He wasn't into such endevors, he had sent his message, so he was finished with it. He expected retaliation, so naturally he continued his usual training. Fighting against his Sproc Warrior alone as he did usually, the 'Fear Kiting' Techinque beign his best ally in this battle. Not a clue that he by change slain the very one he was after from the very beginning.. but he had already achieved the goal of his assults. Nay, he didn't have the trouphy to place infront of all that dared to call his straight forward methods 'Weak' and 'Inneffective', but instead, he showed how weak and cowardly she really was.<br>
